We recommended that Management:

analyze the composition of dormant receivables and prepare the individual or detailed schedule of the accounts; 

determine the collectibility of the accounts and send demand letters to the concerned individuals, suppliers, and/or the heirs of the accountable officers; 

exhaust all applicable legal remedies to collect; 

request for write off of accounts from COA if remedies fail and when necessary; and 

if any, make adjustments in the books, when necessary.

